See NYT of November 12, 1914,
  <a href="http://select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F00612FD3C5C13738DDDAB0994D9415B848DF1D3" rel="nofollow">select.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=F00612FD3C5C1373...</a>
&quot;The Board of Education for fully two hours and a half yesterday afternoon wrestled with the case of Mrs. Lora M. Wagner, the teacher-mother in the Curtis High School. First, it decided by a vote of 25 to 8 against the report of its Committee on High Schools granting her a leave of absence from Nov. 3, 1914, to Sept. 10, 1915, for the purpose of rearing her child. .... &quot;
